---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Learning From the User Without Lock-In"
  description="Improve suggestions and behavior from user feedback and behavior, but let users see, correct, or reset personalization so they don't feel locked in."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Learning without lock-in" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full">
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Transparent Personalization</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >Recommendations are based on: your recent projects, your saved preferences, and similar
            tasks in your team.</mds-text
          >
          <div class="flex gap-200">
            <mds-button variant="outline" size="sm">Edit preferences</mds-button>
            <mds-button variant="outline" size="sm">Reset recommendations</mds-button>
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Users see what drives recommendations and can edit or reset without losing the product.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Corrections Improve Future Suggestions</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >When you reject or edit a suggestion, we use that to improve next time. You can review
            and delete this feedback in Settings â†’ Personalization.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Learning is explicit; users know their corrections are used and can review or clear
            that data.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-status-error-10 border border-status-error-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/error" class="text-status-error-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"><b>Opaque Lock-In (Problematic)</b></mds-text>
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >Recommendations get more personalized over time, but there's no way to see what we
            learned, correct it, or reset. "Personalization" in settings only toggles ads.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-error-06"
            >Users feel trapped by invisible assumptions; wrong inferences are hard to fix; no way
            to start fresh.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>Best Practices</b></mds-text>
          <div class="grid gap-300">
            <div class="p-400 rounded bg-tone-neutral-08">
              <mds-text typography="caption"
                ><b>Do:</b> Let users view, edit, or delete data used for personalization</mds-text
              >
            </div>
            <div class="p-400 rounded bg-tone-neutral-08">
              <mds-text typography="caption"
                ><b>Do:</b> Provide "Reset recommendations" or "Start over" so users can clear learned
                preferences</mds-text
              >
            </div>
            <div class="p-400 rounded bg-tone-neutral-08">
              <mds-text typography="caption"
                ><b>Don't:</b> Learn from behavior in a way that's invisible or impossible to correct</mds-text
              >
            </div>
            <div class="p-400 rounded bg-tone-neutral-08">
              <mds-text typography="caption"
                ><b>Don't:</b> Make personalization a permanent state with no opt-out or reset</mds-text
              >
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Use feedback and behavior to improve suggestions, and make that learning visible and editable.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Personalize in ways that are invisible or that users cannot review, correct, or reset.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Provide "Reset" or "Clear personalization" so users can start fresh without losing the
      product.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Create lock-in where wrong or outdated inferences are hard or impossible to fix.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
